result.execSummary:
The defendant Zachary Scott Germain was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Zachary Scott Germain is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Zachary Scott Germain was found guilty of Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Case called at 8:18 a.m. ADA Collins states this will be a waiver of preliminary hearing.  Requesting bind over and recommendations.   Atty Demaio filed a waiver of preliminary form with the court. Court goes over rights with defendant. Court will accept bind over and finds that defendant knowingly and voluntarily waives preliminary hearing.  State will amend Count 1 to Possess THC 1st offense, misdemeanor.   Court reads charge and maximum penalty. DE pleads GUILTY to amended  Ct 1 in 15CF132 . DE sworn. Crt reviews plea questionnaire and informs DE of rights. Crt finds DE freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights and makes plea. Attorney's stipulate to the facts. Crt accepts plea, finds factual basis and finds DE guilty of amended Ct 1, Possess THC 1st offense, Misd.  in  15CF132 . On motion of the State, Crt dismisses Ct 2 in 15CF132 . Sentencing arguments. Defendant makes statement. Bond will continue until defendant checks into probation. Crt orders:

- S/W. 1 year probation. Report no later than 4 p.m. today

- Misdemeanor court costs

- Follow through with rules and conditions of probation agent
